
create link between files that can be either hard link or soft link

link= is like a short cut to access a file
type 
1.soft link or symbolic link
2. hard link

har link contain same inode value
ln [orgnal filename] [link name]

soft linek caontain seperate inode value
ls -s [orginal filename] [link name]

-------------------

ln command used to creat link fro file in linux
1st form: 
  ln program.py linkfile.py
  ls -liahr

2nd form: creating in a directoy

  ln program.py test_dir/

3rd from

  ln -t test_directory/ example.txt

most useful option for ln command are

ls -v 
-v verbose which helps you know which file is linked to which file
basically it print the name of each linked file

